import { MatPaginatorModule } from "@angular/material/paginator"; import { MatIconModule } from "@angular/material/icon"; import { MatPaginator } from "@angular/material/paginator"; import { MatSort } from "@angular/material/sort"; @ViewChild(MatSort, { static: true }) sort!: MatSort; constructor(private apiService: SubscriberService) { this.apiService.getPagedAllSubscribers().subscribe( (data) => { console.log("DATA:::", data); data.Data = this.dataSource.data; // Assuming the API returns an array of objects console.log("DATA:::", data.Data); this.dataSource.paginator = this.paginator; this.dataSource.sort = this.sort; }, (error) => { console.error("Error fetching data from API:", error); } ); } ngOnInit() { this.apiService.getPagedAllSubscribers().subscribe( (data) => { console.log("DATA:::", data); this.dataSource.data = data.Data; // Assuming the API returns an array of objects console.log("DATA:::", this.dataSource.data); this.dataSource.paginator = this.paginator; this.dataSource.sort = this.sort; }, (error) => { console.error("Error fetching data from API:", error); } ); } // Define the displayed columns displayedColumns: string[] = [ "fullname", "email", "mobilenumber", "created_at", "status", "action", ];
